e="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This was AFTER they "finished" it. They didn't remove all the old wax.  All those scratches and streaks are in the old wax.  The terrazzo is in great condition, considering it's 70 years old.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/t4hlvYt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Soooo much wax.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FItenNb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>It looked like soggy toilet paper. It probably hadn't been completely stripped in a couple of decades.  Just scrubbed and top coated.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xCPRwCn.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Down to bare terrazzo.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6IbKJjB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>5 coats of finish later and finally done.  No more scratches.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/fCSJH8k</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[AvsFreak]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Chemical art</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/NXPDdPh</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kV8bXLg.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>https://youtu.be/OMBFwWTJy-0?si=6USNBMwpve6_rnd6</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/NXPDdPh</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[sjoezer]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>A photo of my dog Panko every day</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/B6h7MT0</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/sRdLjht.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I let Panko use my little heating pad. I think he liked it.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/B6h7MT0</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[PankoBoy]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Jebus</title